    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="966"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d966">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 714.1515/30</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Minister of Guatemala</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 96</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of November 12, expressing your Government’s thanks for the friendly
                    reception accorded to the Special Mission of Guatemala, stating that your
                    Government accepts the mediation offered by the United States in the matter of
                    the boundary dispute between Guatemala and Honduras, and requesting that I
                    recommend to the Government of Honduras that, as a step preliminary to the
                    arbitration, the protocol <pb facs="0950" n="784" xml:id="pg_784"/> recently
                    signed by representatives of Guatemala and Honduras be made effective.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that the Department is giving the
                    contents of your note earnest consideration, and would be glad to receive a copy
                    of the protocol referred to, in order to inform itself as to its terms.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
